description: As markets rally, investors face six behavioural traps that can derail wealth. Overconfidence, panic selling after gains, FOMO-driven entries, succumbing to tips, ignoring diversification, and using borrowed money are highlighted. Prudent investors maintain discipline, stick to strategy, and avoid impulsive decisions to safeguard their long-term financial future.
title: Stock markets at lifetime highs: What should investors do? Six mistakes to avoid

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai heralds 'vibe coding' as a revolutionary force, democratizing tech by empowering non-technical professionals to build applications through simple AI prompts. This shift is already reshaping workplaces, with professionals in diverse fields leveraging tools like ChatGPT and Gemini to create functional prototypes. While acknowledging limitations for critical systems, Pichai expresses immense optimism for AI's future in software development, envisioning a more accessible and enjoyable coding landscape for everyone.
title: Vibe Coding in spotlight: Google CEO on its power for non-tech grads; says it can help them build tech careers

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Delhi's worsening air pollution has sparked criticism, with AAP leader Arvind Kejriwal demanding a cut in GST on air and water purifiers. Congress MP Rahul Gandhi called for a parliamentary debate and an action plan, highlighting the health crisis faced by children breathing toxic air.
title: AQI politics: Kejriwal demands GST cut on purifiers; Rahul calls for Parliament debate

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India's U19 squad for the ACC Men's Asia Cup has been unveiled, with Ayush Mhatre leading the 15-member team. Teen sensation Vaibhav Sooryavanshi headlines the batting lineup. The young brigade faces Pakistan on December 14 in Dubai, aiming to assert dominance in the tournament commencing December 12.
title: Asia Cup: India U19 squad announced; high-stakes Pak clash on Dec 14

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A man's viral video shows him politely urging train passengers to avoid littering, emphasizing personal responsibility for cleanliness. His appeal highlights that individual habits contribute to the perception of India and Bihar being dirty. While some praised his civic sense, others suggested authorities should lead such initiatives.
title: 'Bihar dirty because ... ': Man appeals to train passengers to not litter; video viral

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Enforcement Directorate has alleged that Al-Falah University chancellor Javed Ahmed Siddiqui fraudulently obtained Delhi land by forging documents of deceased Hindu landowners. The agency claims a fake General Power of Attorney, dated 2004, was used to transfer property in Madanpur Khadar to a trust linked to Siddiqui.  The investigation into this alleged land scam is ongoing with Siddiqui in ED custody.
title: Delhi car blast: Al-Falah chancellor forged papers to grab land of deceased Hindu owners

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold price prediction today: Gold prices are showing a bullish bias, trading steady near ₹1,25,540. Technical indicators suggest a buy-on-dips strategy around ₹1,25,500, with support at ₹1,25,350 and resistance at ₹1,25,850. Investors are advised to maintain a stop-loss below ₹1,25,250 for potential upside targets.
title: Gold price prediction: What's the outlook for Nov 28? Here's what investors should do

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin is scheduled to visit India on December 4-5 for a summit with Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Discussions are expected to focus on India's potential procurement of additional S-400 air-defense squadrons and Sukhoi-57 fighter jets. The ongoing Russia-Ukraine war will also be a key agenda item, with India reiterating its support for an early peaceful resolution.
title: Putin-Modi meet: Russian president to visit India on December 4; what's on agenda?

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Swiggy has vehemently denied reports claiming its quick-commerce arm, Instamart, lost market share to Zepto. The company stated that claims citing HSBC and Redseer data are "baseless and unreliable," with Redseer itself confirming no data was shared. This rebuttal underscores the intense competition for the second position in India's quick-commerce market.
title: Swiggy 'categorically and strongly' denies data claiming it has lost No. 2 position to Zepto; issues clarification on BSE with 'email proof'

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Phoebe Gates, daughter of billionaire Bill Gates, shares her unique childhood. She and her siblings used their mother Melinda French Gates' surname, French, until high school. This parenting choice aimed to shield them from wealth's influence and allow genuine connections.
title: Bill Gates’ daughter on identity and school life; why using her mother’s last name helped; reveals the reason

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Five international flights bound for Sri Lanka were diverted to Thiruvananthapuram International Airport on Friday due to bad weather and a cyclone warning over Colombo. Flights from Dubai, Doha, Abu Dhabi, Kuala Lumpur, and Mumbai landed safely. Separately, an Air India flight returned to Delhi after a false smoke warning in its cargo hold.
title: Cyclone Ditwah alert: 4 Colombo-bound flights diverted to Trivandrum

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Following India's Test series loss to South Africa, Gautam Gambhir's coaching is under fire. Former cricketer AB de Villiers suggested Gambhir's emotional nature as a player might translate to his coaching, potentially unsettling the team. While acknowledging no single coaching formula works, De Villiers contrasted this with South Africa's calm coach, highlighting varied player preferences for leadership styles.
title: IND vs SA: 'Emotional coach' - AB de Villiers' explosive verdict on Gautam Gambhir

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Delhi Police have apprehended Bandhu Maan Singh Shekhon, a key operative of the Goldy Dhillon gang, in connection with the shootings at Kapil Sharma's Canadian cafe.  Shekhon allegedly coordinated the overseas attacks from India.  The cafe faced three shooting incidents and Molotov cocktail attacks, with gangs claiming responsibility and issuing further threats, including one targeting Mumbai.
title: Kapil Sharma’s Cafe shootings: Mastermind arrested by Delhi Police

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: Delhi Police's crime branch has arrested Bandhu Maan Singh Shekhon, a key member of the Goldy Dhillon gang, in connection with multiple shootings at Kapil Sharma's Kap's Cafe in Canada. The incidents, claimed by the Lawrence Bishnoi gang, involved firing shots and hurling Molotov cocktails, with a Chinese pistol seized during the arrest.
title: Kap's cafe shooting in Canada: Main conspirator of Goldy Dhillon gang arrested

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Karnataka's chief ministerial post sees intensified tussle between Siddaramaiah and DK Shivakumar camps. Both leaders defer to the Congress high command, while political signalling and speculation about a power-sharing arrangement continue. Key developments include meetings and community group support for Shivakumar, alongside his son's backing of the current CM.
title: Sidda vs DKS: Power-sharing tussle rages in Karnataka Congress; top developments

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The BJP has mocked the Congress's internal power struggle in Karnataka, calling it an "OTT series of 'Congress vs Congress'."  BJP leader Shehzad Poonawalla criticized the party's focus on "power, the chair, and leadership" over public issues.  This comes amid a public exchange between CM Siddaramaiah and Deputy CM DK Shivakumar regarding leadership and promises.
title: ‘Words & worlds revolving ...: BJP mocks K'taka tussle; takes ‘Congress vs Congress’ dig

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: The New York Mets are reportedly eyeing San Diego Padres pitcher Michael King as their next major acquisition following Dylan Cease's record-breaking contract. King, who excelled as a starter before a mid-season injury, now represents a high-upside option for the Mets amidst a shifting pitching market.  His potential return to peak form makes him an intriguing target.
title: MLB rumors: Mets could target $15M Padres starter after Dylan Cease deal

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: Despite facing career-threatening injuries and two surgeries, Abhishek Reddy's unwavering determination fueled his return to cricket.  A remarkable 247 in the Ranji Trophy against Jharkhand marked his triumphant comeback, proving his enduring passion.  Inspired by Sachin Tendulkar, Reddy's journey highlights resilience and the pursuit of dreams against all odds.
title: 2 surgeries, years on hospital beds: Abhishek Reddy's incredible comeback

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Uttar Pradesh has declared Aadhaar cards invalid as proof of birth date, with the Planning Department issuing a directive to all state departments. This decision comes amidst broader actions by Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath to identify and deport illegal immigrants, including the establishment of temporary detention centers in each district.
title: 'Aadhaar no longer accepted as proof of birth': New order in UP and Maharashtra

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi woke to a thick smog blanket as winter sets in, with the AQI reaching 384, categorizing it as 'Very Poor'. Several areas reported 'Severe' levels, exceeding 400. While authorities lifted Stage III restrictions, vigilance under earlier stages continues to prevent further deterioration. Residents noted increased pollution, with one attributing it to volcanic ash.
title: Air emergency in Delhi: AQI remains 'very poor'; Anand Vihar clocks 408

author: TNN
description: Cyclone Ditwah is poised to bring heavy rainfall to north Tamil Nadu, with red alerts issued for delta and coastal districts on November 28-29. Chennai and neighboring areas face orange alerts for heavy to very heavy rain on November 29-30. Wind speeds are expected to reach 60-80kmph, with potential for extremely heavy downpours in specific locations.
title: Cyclone Ditwah alert: Storm may hit Tamil Nadu in 2 days; IMD upgrades alerts to red

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US President Donald Trump announced plans to permanently halt migration from "Third World Countries" to allow the US system to recover. He further linked this decision to an alleged White House shooting incident involving an Afghan national and the US evacuation from Afghanistan, citing concerns about unvetted individuals entering the country.
title: 'Will permanently pause migration': Trump's big warning to 'Third World Countries'

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Candace Owens' explosive claims on X, alleging French President Macron and his wife paid for her assassination and French Legion soldiers killed Charlie Kirk, have been met with skepticism. Right-wing commentator Nick Fuentes publicly demanded proof, calling her stories 'crazy' and lacking evidence, particularly mocking her claims about Brigitte Macron's family history and gender.
title: Nick Fuentes seeks proof after Candace Owens links deaths to alleged plot

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Croma's Black Friday Sale offers the iPhone 17 at an effective Rs 45,900, a significant reduction from its Rs 82,900 launch price. This deal, valid until November 30, 2025, combines bank cashback, substantial exchange value, and a fixed bonus.  It makes Apple's latest non-Pro model more accessible, featuring a 120Hz ProMotion display and the A19 chip.
title: Apple iPhone 17 available for Rs 45,900 in Croma Black Friday Sale: Know how to grab the deal

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump criticized the Biden administration's immigration policies, blaming them for the recent shooting near the White House. He asserted that the administration allowed unvetted individuals to enter the US, including the suspect in the shooting, Rahmanullah Lakanwal. Trump also reiterated his criticism of the Afghanistan withdrawal, calling it a mess and a mistake.
title: 'Are you a stupid person?': Trump slams reporter questioning him over White House shooting

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A war of words erupted between Congress and BJP after former MP Kumar Ketkar alleged US and Israeli intelligence agencies meddled in the 2014 elections. BJP MP Sambit Patra countered, attributing BJP's victories to public support and accusing Congress of following Pakistan's ISI agenda.
title: 'Both had to do something in India': Congress leader claims CIA–Mossad behind 2014 rout

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Diogo Jota's widow, Rute Cardoso, shared an emotional first-birthday tribute to their baby daughter, posting poignant photos of the late Liverpool star. The images, including five with Jota, have evoked widespread love and grief, underscoring the profound impact of his tragic death. Jota died in a car crash just weeks after marrying Rute, leaving behind their three children.
title: Daughter's 1st birthday: Diogo Jota's widow posts heartbreaking tribute

author: DWAIPAYAN DATTA
description: India's Test cricket legacy is rapidly declining, particularly at home, as the focus shifts to white-ball glory from junior levels. This prioritization of T20 and ODI formats has led to a neglect of red-ball skills, with junior selectors and players alike prioritizing white-ball success, impacting the development of Test specialists.
title: IND vs SA: Is India bothered about Test debacle?

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Former IPS officer Kiran Bedi has voiced grave concerns over Delhi's hazardous air quality, with the AQI reaching alarming levels. She highlighted the severe health impacts and the need for stronger political leadership, advocating for Prime Minister's intervention to coordinate multi-state efforts.
title: ‘It’s like Covid’: Kiran Bedi flags Delhi pollution crisis; claims AQI hits 587 in Indirapuram

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened flat in trade on Friday. While Nifty50 was above 26,200, BSE Sensex was near 85,750.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens flat; BSE Sensex near 85,750

author: ALOKKNMISHRA
description: Since Jan 2024, the Delhi Commission for Women has had no chairperson, and no members since July 2024. In May 2024, Women and Child Development dept ordered removal of 223 contractual staffers over “improper” hiring . The last chairperson, Swati Maliwal, resigned after being elected to the Rajya Sabha in Jan 2024.
title: 'Bandh hai’: Once a lifeline for distressed women, Delhi Mahila Aayog lies defunct

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Former Pakistani Prime Minister Imran Khan's son alleges his father is held in a death cell with no transparency. Kasim Khan states there have been no calls or meetings, and no proof of life. Khan's sisters have been denied visits despite court orders. The family urges international intervention and proof of life.
title: 'No proof of life': Imran Khan’s son sparks new round of doubts amid death rumours

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Nikki Haley's son, Nalin, expressed a strong stance against immigration, stating he feels no "weird loyalty" to countries he hasn't visited. He argued that legal immigration is irresponsible given the current "fragile economy" and job displacement by AI, advocating for prioritizing American workers.
title: 'Not gonna have weird loyalty …': Nikki Haley’s son distances from Indian roots

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A heartwarming video of MS Dhoni driving Virat Kohli back to his hotel after a private dinner at Dhoni's Ranchi residence has gone viral. The rare sight, with no security, evoked nostalgia for their decade-long partnership. Kohli is in Ranchi for the ODI series against South Africa, marking his return to the city.
title: 'Reunion of the Year': Dhoni drives Kohli back after dinner in Ranchi - video

author: SANDEEP RAI
description: A Delhi man was apprehended in Uttar Pradesh for attempting to defraud an insurance company by presenting a mannequin as his deceased employee. He planned to cremate the dummy, obtain a death certificate, and claim a Rs 50 lakh insurance policy to clear his debts. The employee, unaware of the plot, was contacted by police.
title: Delhi man takes dummy ‘corpse’ to funeral to fake employee death, claim insurance

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A Delhi doctor warns that zero-sugar products can be misleading, potentially causing overeating and harming gut health. Artificial sweeteners and refined ingredients in diet foods may trigger insulin spikes and increase cravings, despite lacking calories. Experts advise prioritizing whole, minimally processed foods for better metabolic wellness and sustainable weight management.
title: Hidden dangers of sugar-free snacks on gut health, insulin, and weight gain

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: An Indian-origin Sikh man, claiming US citizenship, was denied entry into Canada by a border officer due to a prior criminal record. The man accused the officer of religious discrimination, but the officer explained the decision was based on Canadian databases and laws, not his religion or origin. The video of the interaction that the man recorded went viral.
title: 'You have criminal record': Sikh man stopped from entering Canada from US

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Fatty liver can creep up on you without any overt symptoms, but your body may be sending out warning signs. According to Dr. Saurabh Sethi, unexpected weight gain around the belly, increased blood sugar levels, darker urine, ongoing fatigue, and discomfort in the upper abdomen are all red flags.
title: Fatty Liver Warning Signs: Don't Ignore These 8 Symptoms

author: TNN
description: The Income Tax Department has launched a fresh campaign targeting individuals with undeclared overseas assets and income.  Around 25,000 high-risk cases will be initially contacted via SMS and email. This initiative aims to encourage taxpayers to review and revise their returns by December 31 to avoid significant penalties under the Black Money Act.
title: Fresh I-T push: 25k flagged for foreign assets, income; advised to review returns by Dec 31

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: South Africa dominated the Test through strong batting contributions led by Senuran Muthusamy’s maiden century and Marco Jansen’s explosive 93. Jansen, who also took 6/48 in the first innings, dismantled India’s batting order before Simon Harmer completed the rout with a match-winning 6/37 in the second innings.  South Africa sealed a commanding 408-run win, with Harmer finishing as Player of the Series for his 17 wickets across two Tests, while Jansen claimed the Player of the Match award for his all-round brilliance.
title: IND vs SA: 'The biggest fault' - Harbhajan Singh lashes out at Team India

author: DHANANJAY.MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court suggested a law similar to the SC/ST Act to protect differently-abled individuals from ridicule. While the government acknowledged the concern, it raised potential issues for creative artists. The court also directed comedians to host shows featuring SMA achievers, contributing earnings to patient treatment.
title: SC to govt: Consider law to curb ridiculing of disabled; centre flags impact on artists

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Watch: Zohran Mamdani does the iconic SRK pose while guessing Bollywood songs

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A devastating fire ripped through Hong Kong's Wang Fuk Court apartment complex, claiming 94 lives and leaving scores unaccounted for. Firefighters battled the blaze for two days amidst severe obstacles, with the fire believed to have started in scaffolding. Investigations are underway as residents report a lack of fire alarms.
title: Hong Kong high-rise blaze: Death toll climbs to 94 - latest developments

author: JYOTIRMOY HALDER
description: Uzbekistan's Javokhir Sindarov, a 19-year-old, became the youngest World Cup winner, securing a spot in the 2026 Candidates. India, hosting the event after 23 years, saw its 24 players fail to reach the top three qualifying spots. The article explores the knockout format's challenges, home advantage pressures, and the impact of chess engines on creativity.
title: Multi-layered problem: Why no Indians made Candidates 2026 via Goa WC

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tragedy struck near the White House as a National Guard soldier, Sarah Beckstrom, succumbed to injuries from a shooting. President Trump announced her death, stating the second soldier is critically wounded. The alleged attacker, an Afghan national with prior CIA ties, is also injured and will face severe repercussions. The incident prompted lockdowns of nearby federal buildings.
title: National Guard troop shot near White House dies; second victim critical, Trump says

author: DHANANJAY.MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court has directed the Information and Broadcasting Ministry to draft a mechanism for pre-screening user-generated content on social media. The court emphasized the need for a preventive measure to curb the rapid spread of potentially damaging or anti-national content before it goes viral, acknowledging the limitations of post-takedown actions.
title: SC to govt: Need to pre-screen social media content; warns of viral ‘damage’ risk
